page.title: 06Ecology
page.content: Throughout the year it is possible to see at least 100 different species of birds in the area. Some are spring and autumn migrating birds of passage, mainly appearing in small numbers and probably for very brief spells. Many others are with us during summer time only, travelling thousands of miles from their winter habitats in Africa to breed here. These include the fish eating osprey which has, during the last decade become a regular annual visitor (an old Scots Pine being its chosen nesting place),the cuckoo,spotted fly catcher, sedge, willow and white-throat warblers, whin-chat, swifts, swallows and house martins.
